        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 4:41PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 440 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 20 miles northwest of Crescent Lake to 7 miles
east of Lima. Movement was east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
West Yellowstone, Lima, Monida, Big Sky, Bannack Pass, Lakeview,
Yellowstone Village, Targhee Pass, Cameron, Snowline, Red Rock Pass,
Raynolds Pass, and Monida Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
